clinical_study.brief_title: Human Chorionic Gonadotropin Versus Granulocyte Colony Stimulating Factor in Increasing Pregnancy Rate in ICSI
clinical_study.official_title: Intra Uterine Injection of Human Chorionic Gonadotropin Versus Granulocyte Colony Stimulating Factor at Ovum Pick up Day Significantly Increase Implantation Rate and Pregnancy Rate in Intra Cytoplasmic Sperm Injection

brief_summary.textblock: Intrauterine Granulocyte colony stimulating factor (GCSF) was compared with intrauterine Human Chorionic Gonadotropin (HCG) in increasing clinical pregnancy rate as a primary outcome and ultrasound imaging of gestational sac as a secondary outcome.

detailed_description.textblock: Two hundred females with history of recurrent implantation failure and undergoing Intracytoplasmic Sprem injection (ICSI) were randomized into two groups; the first group (100 patients) received intrauterine Granulocyte colony stimulating factor (GCSF) and the second group (100) received intrauterine Human Chorionic Gonadotropin (HCG) at ovum pick up day. The clinical pregnancy rate was evaluated as a primary outcome after 14 days and ultrasound imaging of gestational sac was evaluated as a secondary outcome after 6 weeks.

primary_outcome.time_frame: after 14 days from positive pregnancy test
primary_outcome.description: Clinical pregnancy was evaluated by high HCG levels

secondary_outcome.description: ultrasound imaging of Gestational sac after 6 weeks of pregnancy

arm_group.description: Granulocyte Colony Stimulated Factor was intrauterine injected once at ovum pick up day
500 IU Human Chorionic Gonadotropins was injected intrauterine once at ovum pick up day

intervention.description: GCSF was intrauterine injected once at ovum pick up day
500 IU of HCG was injected intrauterine once at ovum pick up day

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Females suffering from recurrent implantation failure and undergoing ICSI
Exclusion Criteria:
- presence of comorbidity as diabetes, hypertension, heart diseases, or endocrine disorders
